---
import Heading from "@components/Heading.astro";
import HeadingLarge from "@components/HeadingLarge.astro";
import Text from "@components/Text.astro";
import View from "@components/View.astro";
import Group from "@components/Group.astro";
import { Layout } from "@layouts";
import Image from "@components/Image.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Origami | Jonathon Toon | Software Designer, Product Leader"
  description="Jonathon Toon is a versatile software designer and product leader based in Aotearoa New Zealand."
  keywords="design, software, product, fractional, leadership, new zealand, aotearoa, technology, typescript, start ups, engineering, mentorship, coaching, adplist"
  twitterHandle="@jonathontoon"
  canonicalUrl="https://www.jonathontoon.com/"
  ogImage="/images/og-image.png"
>
  <Group>
    <HeadingLarge class="px-2">Origami</HeadingLarge>
    <Text class="px-2">
      Founded in 2012 as a mobile ecommerce platform, Origami pivoted to focus on mobile payments
      in Japan's cash-dominant market, some time before Apple Pay arrived. Japanese consumers were
      naturally skeptical of digital payments when cash ruled daily life.
    </Text>
    <Text class="px-2">
      I joined as a designer when I moved to Japan in 2015, expanding the design
      team to three people. I worked on feature updates before moving into prototyping
      payment experiences tailored for this unique market.
    </Text>
    <Text class="px-2">
      What I discovered was that assumptions about "good design" don't translate across cultures.
      What feels intuitive varies dramatically by context, environment and values.
    </Text>
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <View class="px-2">
      <View class="h-px w-full bg-stone-200 dark:bg-stone-700" />
    </View>
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <Heading class="px-2">Pay</Heading>
    <Text class="px-2">
      One of the company's moonshots was using Bluetooth technology to enable seamless payments.
      I worked closely with an iOS engineer, with regular feedback from the CEO, to prototype the experience in code.
      Our goal was to make purchases feel enjoyable and effortless.
    </Text>
    <Text class="px-2">
      During the design phase I also added a way for customers rate their in-store experience.
      This became valuable for store owners, who could learn more about their customers, beyond purchase history.
    </Text>
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <Image
      src="/images/work/origami-pay.png"
      alt="Mobile payment flow optimized for Japanese market preferences."
      class="w-full rounded-xl bg-stone-200 dark:bg-stone-800"
      lightbox={true}
    />
    <Image
      src="/images/work/origami-ipad-payment.png"
      alt="Mobile payment flow optimized for Japanese market preferences."
      class="w-full rounded-xl bg-stone-200 dark:bg-stone-800"
      lightbox={true}
    />
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <Heading class="px-2">Navigation</Heading>
    <Text class="px-2">
      With pop-up promotions for Origami happening in malls and shopping centers across the country, we needed a way for people to
      experience payments without account creation barriers.
    </Text>
    <Text class="px-2">
      To help with this I redesigned the navigation to prioritize the core functions: payments, cards, receipts. This, in addition to a guest browsing mode, let people immediately understand the core value,
      while moving ecommerce browsing to a secondary tab.
    </Text>
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <Image
      src="/images/work/origami-navigation.png"
      alt="Navigation system designed for single-handed mobile usage patterns."
      class="w-full rounded-xl bg-stone-200 dark:bg-stone-800"
      lightbox={true}
    />
  </Group>
</Layout>
